reviewText:
Before I go on any further, let it be plainly known that this collection is, for all intents and purposes, simply the six Mega Man games released for the NES, exactly as they were at release, with simple HD upscaling (so it looks good and has no screen tearing on modern monitors) and various treats for fans.  It does not exist as some end-all be-all collection with tons of amazing extra features or all the games or anything like that.

it does not have:

- a huge amount of Mega Man games or even nearly all of them in the classic series;
- HD remakes or total overhauls of the games;
- any fixes or alterations to the original games; there is still slowdown when too many sprites are onscreen, all the bugs are still there (which can be seen as a good thing, especially with MM1's pause trick still intact) and spelling errors (Wiley" in MM3

hoursPlayed:
 it does have:

- well-done HD upscaling that is smooth as silk and has absolutely no screen-tearing unlike any emulator I've ever used on an HD monitor;
- a very tight and lagless feel closer to playing the games on the original hardware or 3DS

column16:
 one for each game (and of course passwords work too);
- options for screen size and borders on or off as well as some neat stuff like a filter that makes the screen look like an old CRT TV from the 80s;
- a cute little jukebox that lets you listen to any music or jingle from any of the games;
- perhaps most importantly
